6:
Wh-where are we?! This doesn't look
like Palpebra at all.
10:
Talk about a glitzy town. Got
anything, Stella?
14:
I have the coordinates. However, the
World Flipper's location is slightly
unclear.
17:
It seems we've yet again wandered
into an unfamiliar world. I haven't
seen any view quite like this one,
however.
24:
Two organics. One mutant. Both
unregistered, including their
armaments and clothing.
27:
Based on this information, the
probability they are related to the
pillar of light is quite high.
Recommending securing the
subjects.
33:
Surrender immediately—attempting
to resist will subject you to
disciplinary measures.
41:
Attempts to initiate dialogue are not
permitted.
48:
Resistance confirmed. Destroy
armaments and retrieve—
55:
Would love to chat, but not
here—come with me if you wanna
live. Got it?
59:
Seems we've got no choice... Let us
make haste!
65:
Honestly, I was thinking some sort of
new mutant or whatever had
escaped, but...
68:
This is WAY cooler! Visitors from
another world?! NOW we're talking!
72: Thank you for your assistance, friend.
74:
Could you tell us where we've
landed? And what sort of place is
this, exactly?
77:
Welcome, friends, to Qualia City. As
for what kind of place this is... just
look around you.
81:
This city's engine runs on the blood
of capitalism and greed—a world
where anything and everything is
dominated by giant corporations.
85:
So in lieu of politicians, the world is
governed by corporate entities and
businesses?
88:
Politicians? Now that's a throwback.
But yes, each and every corporation
is its own nation. And each of the
employees a citizen.
90:
But within this machine caked in
blood is a bullet that flies free...
93:
That's right—me! The name's Bulleta.
Troubleshooter.
95:
You sure talk big for someone who
just had trouble dealing with their
air bill.
98:
What was that?! An illusionary spell,
like those images in the sky?
103:
No, those are merely pop-ups. I'm
something entirely different.
108:
Her name's Love. You can count on
her to hack into pretty much
anything, anywhere!
116:
It's nice to meet you both, Love and
Bulleta.
119:
Likewise! So, Love. About this "World
Flipper" these fellows are looking for—
123:
Wouldn't it be more important for
them to find a way of accruing
credits first?
126:
Surely the so-called "Freedom
Blaster" isn't going to let these
strangers starve, right?
129:
What I mean to say is, you folks are
gonna need some capital if you
plan on surviving here.
131:
I recommend you become
troubleshooters like Bulleta and
myself in order to get some cash.
134:
I suppose it would behoove us to
find our bearings first... So, what is a
troubleshooter, exactly? And how do
we get started?
137:
You complete the request given to
you. And not die during the process.
That's all there is to it.
141:
I guess it's sort of like our Guild, in a
way. So where do we go to sign up?
148:
A request just came in, actually. It
seems a drone has gone haywire
and needs someone to subdue it.
151:
With the Network, you can
communicate anywhere and
anytime.
153:
But the actual work itself is as
primitive as you'd expect—that
sword isn't just for show, right?
157:
I don't think so? Either way, I'll try not
to slow you down.
160:
That's the spirit! Now let's get
moving—that bounty isn't gonna
catch itself!
167: She never turns off, does she?
